[thinking] **Clarifying abstract class handling**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I need to ensure that a sealed abstract class has its direct children in the same file. If the companion object isn’t containing the necessary entries, maybe the public API could define those entries in the same scope? I wonder about the order of values—should it follow the source declaration? For top-level entries appearing before the companion, it would be first and second. But what happens if they come after the companion? Maybe the macro in companion expansion can access definitions later?
