rage. \\n\\nI'll think about adding a JUnit test using the Scala compiler's public API, but running that in a native image might be burdensome, especially with startup times. The test needs to be quick, ideally under 60 seconds, and needs careful consideration around class loading and macro use.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Scala testing and reflection**\\n\\nI’m contemplating whether to use a Scala test with the public API and direct reflection to its generated lambda. I could write a test that utilizes Java reflection to access fields dynamically. However, I’m thinking that the active class may not be covered, and I might need a method accessible through `MethodHandles`. It seems I’m hitting a wall with accessing method names statically in Java.\\n\\nPerhaps using Scala's reflection with backticks might help, but typechecking doesn't recognize methods easily. There’s a possibility that TASTy might have private methods hidden from view, which could lead to compile failures.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Java class integration in Scala**\\n\\nI'm trying to figure out if I can add a Java class in a Scala file. It seems like that’s not feasible. I want to use reflection to access a specific method, but I’m running into complications because there’s no `$` in the test class or file. While strings can have `$`, it looks like the rule only applies to names. So, I need to rethink my approach to access the method correctly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NtqhR5SWF9hthoyHW8WxV6Yo|fc_08901812d79efd2d016a3d9abdf64481979a2d0d5f5c2c0f8a", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/1.9.0/src/test/scala/com_beachape/enumeratum_macros_3/ValueEnumMacrosTest.scala", "edits": [{"oldText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertSame\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n", "newText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertSame\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method\n"}, {"oldText": "    assertEquals(None, TopLevelHttpStatus.withValueOpt(500))\n  }\n}\n\nsealed abstract class TopLevelHttpStatus(val value: Int) extends IntEnumEntry\n", "newText": "    assertEquals(None, TopLevelHttpStatus.withValueOpt(500))\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def valueOfFromExprModuleFieldReaderReturnsTheModuleSingleton(): Unit = {\n    val moduleField: Field = ValueEnumMacroModuleHolder.getClass.getField(\"MODULE$\")\n    val moduleReader: Method = Class\n      .forName(\"enumeratum.ValueEnumMacros$\")\n      .getDeclaredMethod(\n        \"enumeratum$ValueEnumMacros$ValueOfFromExpr$$_$unapply$$anonfun$adapted$1\",\n        classOf[Field]\n      )\n    val valueOf: ValueOf[ValueEnumMacroModuleHolder.type] =\n      moduleReader.invoke(null, moduleField).asInstanceOf[ValueOf[ValueEnumMacroModuleHolder.type]]\n\n    assertSame(ValueEnumMacroModuleHolder, valueOf.value)\n  }\n}\n\nsealed abstract class TopLevelHttpStatus(val value: Int) extends IntEnumEntry\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 914, "output": 1652, "cacheRead": 57344, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 59910, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782422180247, "responseId": "resp_08901812d79efd2d016a3d9aa499688197859e3c771ef343e7"}}
